        <abstract>
            <p>Thanks HL for his kind note, the interesting notice, &amp; the photograph.</p> 
<p>He has made a mistake about the <hi rend="italic">Lepas</hi>. It is the <hi rend="italic">L. australis</hi> that is confined to the S. Hemisphere. <hi rend="italic">L. hillii</hi> is found all over the world. Refers HL to <hi rend="italic">Living Cirripedia</hi> [1851].</p> 
        </abstract>
